      Information Physics theory
    </h3>

    <div class="mb-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/field-guide"
        title="Information Physics Field Guide: Start Here"
        description="From maximum-entropy environments to observer-dependent mathematics for embedded consciousness. The discovery journey revealing how physical conscious beings navigate Shannon's information-entropy through thermodynamic constraints."
      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/theory"
        title="Information Physics Theory"
        description="A physics of conscious systems describing how entropy is navigated by embedded, thermodynamically constrained agents. Explains how human systems evolve, stabilize, or collapse through position-dependent entropy dynamics from individuals to civilizations."
      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/conservation-of-boundaries"
        title="Universal Law: Conservation of Boundaries"
        description="All system change occurs through exactly three operations: MOVE, JOIN, SEPARATE. Learn the universal law governing how boundaries transform and why the same mechanics that build can destroy."
      />
