      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/entropic-gap"
        title="Entropic Gap: Mathematical Precision for Measuring Vector Deviation"
        description="Detect system decay before it becomes catastrophic. Calculate the exact distance between what your system should be versus what it's become using vector mathematics. Transform reactive management into proactive maintenance."
      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/entropic-equilibrium"
        title="Entropic Equilibrium: Why Systems Stabilize Where They Do"
        description="From game theory to entropic exhaustion, discover why systems stabilize when they do. Learn how Nash Equilibrium actually forms through observer-dependent optimization and why different positions create different realities."
      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/in-mathematics"
        title="Information Physics in Mathematics"
        description="Observer-dependent mathematics for conscious beings as physical entities subject to thermodynamic constraints. Building on Shannon's information-entropy equivalence where position, heat, fatigue determine calculation outcomes."
      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/in-science"
        title="Information Physics in Science"
        description="Building on Shannon's information-entropy equivalence to create observer-dependent mathematics for embedded consciousness. From quantum mechanics to biology, the same thermodynamic constraints on conscious beings appear at every scale."
      />
      <ContentCard
        slug="/information-physics/throughout-history"
        title="Information Physics Throughout History"
        description="Sun Tzu, Machiavelli, and Napoleon intuited what we now can prove. Explore how history's greatest strategists applied Information Physics principles centuries before we had the mathematics."
      />
    </div>

    <div class="my-24 flex justify-center">
      <div class="w-1/2 h-1 bg-honey-crusted-chicken rounded-full"></div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-4xl font-semibold mb-8 text-raptures-light" id="guides">
      The Developer Advocate's Guides
    </h3>

    {/* Repeat this pattern for each ContentCard */}
    <div class="mb-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <ContentCard
        slug="/blog/developer-advocates-guide-to-metrics-and-reporting"
        title="The Developer Advocate's Guide to Metrics and Reporting"
